                      "quantity_236": ",DA/DE"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "In the triton spectrum are the ground state of Be-8",
                "and the excited states at 2.9 MeV and at 11.9 MeV are",
                "noticeable as peaks, whereas the region of the spectrum",
                "between 4.MeV and 9.MeV triton-energy can be associated",
                "as simultaneous break-up into three particles or with",
                "the sequential process",
                "neutron + B-10 = alpha + Li 7(4.63MeV)",
                "                         Li 7(4.63MeV) = triton + alpha",
                "See accession number 30103.005 for ratio of partial",
                "cross sections"
              ]
            }
          ],
